node.text:
We’re so excited to announce Noma Projects and the launch of Project 001, noma’s line of garums, coming later this year. This is the culmination of 18 years of knowledge, craft and experimentation channeled into a new endeavor. To bring Project 001 to life, we collaborated with design agency @gretelnyc and one of our long-time favorite artists, @davidshrigley . For first access to preorders and news on upcoming projects, visit the link in bio! 

Music: @stefanpasborg / Ibrahim Electric
DOP: Mathias Nyholm Schmidt 
Editor: Rasmus Nyholm Schmidt

node.text:
The seemingly impossible has happened. 

Noma got the news today that the Michelin Guide has given us their highest praise of three Michelin stars.

To us, this is an achievement that solidifies Copenhagen as one of the best places in the world for restaurants right now.

We want to thank our wonderful guests for their support over the last 18 years and a huge shout of course to all our collaborators—farmers, winemakers, foragers—everyone that’s been a part of our giant puzzle, and most of all our team both past and present.

node.text:
Yesterday the test kitchen team—Mette, Mirek and Jun, along with Rene—reviewed the full game & forest menu for the first time.

It’s a critical first step in finalizing next season’s menu, where every detail is considered—from plating, to sequence, and down to the utensils we’ll use for each course.

Tasting will continue over the next few days to fine tune these details, which will then include wine and juice pairings.

Game & Forest season begins on September 23rd, and while we’re always a little sad to see summer go, we look forward to the warmth and glow of crisp fall days…and introducing our new menu to you.

node.text:
We’re searching for a new member to join our Fermentation Lab as Head of Production. 

With the launch of Noma Projects and ongoing activities here at noma, we have a number of exciting new initiatives ahead and we’re looking for a senior manager to join our team. 
 
This individual should have a passion for fermentation, nature, science, and be driven by creativity. An in-depth knowledge of fermentation processing and large-scale culinary production with a minimum of three years’ experience is required. This role requires strong leadership skills and the ability to work and create in a fast-paced environment. The ideal candidate will excel in writing, communication, and culinary research and development.

If this sounds like you, please send a cover letter and CV to Traci at tpm@noma.dk

node.text:
Late summer harvest—

We’re relishing these final days of our summer menu while looking forward to what’s to come…

From our summer juice pairing - 

Cold infused Malawi Antlers and cherry blossoms from our friends @rareteacompany , blended with a mirabelle blossom kombucha. The blossoms were lovingly hand-picked by our front of house team in May, when they were first in bloom. 

Swipe to learn more about what makes this tea so special.
